<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1436,1191,1360]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">
<materialsCitation ID-GBIF-Occurrence="1300284312" country="Liberia" location="Afrotropical region" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" specimenCount="1">
The genus 
<taxonomicName box="[278,385,1192,1216]" class="Arachnida" family="Aturidae" genus="Albaxona" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Trombidiformes" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[278,385,1192,1216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Albaxona</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known from the Palaearctic, Afrotropical, Oriental and Nearctic regions. Two subgenera have been described, based on the fusion or separation of the genital field with the fourth coxae. However, according to 
<bibRefCitation author="Pesi" box="[299,561,1263,1288]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" refString="Pesic, V. &amp; Gerecke, R. (2003) Water mites of the genera Albaxona, Axonopsis, Barbaxonella and Erebaxonopsis (Acari, Hydrachnidia: Aturidae: Axonopsinae) from Central Europe and the Mediterranean area. Archiv fur Hydrobiologie, Supplement, 139, 563 - 578." type="journal article" year="2003">Pe≈°i &amp; Gerecke (2003)</bibRefCitation>
, this fusion is not suitable for discrimination of the subgenera. Consequently, the genus is now without subgeneric classification. From the 
<location LSID="urn:lsid:plazi:treatment:92673E50FFC93505C3ED5476FE177357:1F11D99DFFC93505C02A5503FBB9732A" box="[848,1066,1300,1325]" country="Liberia" name="Afrotropical region" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Afrotropical region</location>
only one species is known from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,232,1335,1360]" name="Liberia" pageId="7" pageNumber="530">Liberia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Cook" box="[246,376,1335,1360]" pageId="7" pageNumber="530" refString="Cook, D. R. (1966) The water mites of Liberia. Memoirs of the American Entomological Institute, 6, 1 - 418." type="journal article" year="1966">Cook 1966</bibRefCitation>
).
</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
